First, note that: \[ 888,888 = 8 \times \frac{10^6 - 1}{9} \] \[ 9,999,999 = 10^7 - 1 \] Thus, we can write: \[ N = 888,888 \times 9,999,999 = \left(8 \times \frac{10^6 - 1}{9}\right) \times (10^7 - 1) \] Simplifying the product: \[ N = \frac{8}{9} \times (10^6 - 1) \times (10^7 - 1) \] \[ N = \frac{8}{9} \times (10^{13} - 10^6 - 10^7 + 1) \] \[ N = \frac{8}{9} \times (10^{13} - 10^7 - 10^6 + 1) \] However, a more straightforward approach is to recognize: \[ 888,888 \times 9,999,999 = 888,888 \times (10,000,000 - 1) \] \[ = 888,888 \times 10,000,000 - 888,888 \] \[ = 8,888,880,000,000 - 888,888 \] \[ = 8,888,879,111,112 \] Next, we sum the digits of the resulting number \( 8,888,879,111,112 \): - The digits are: 8, 8, 8, 8, 8, 7, 9, 1, 1, 1, 1, 2 - Summing these digits: \[ 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 8 + 7 + 9 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 2 = 62 \] Thus, the sum of the digits of \( N \) is \(\boxed{62}\).
